headquarters_regions: Greater Miami Area, East Coast, Southern US
full_description: Almaya offers an innovative solution to the age-old problem of preserving the essence of individuals and their life stories. We are on a mission to ensure that the human experience is securely preserved for the current and future generations. Our core offerings include: A) An 'interactive autobiography builder' app that empowers users to easily record their life's story and engage in a game-like experience, answering questions and prompts about their lives. B) An AI-powered chat (ALMA) that guides friends and family members to interact with the storyteller by asking them questions and receiving their answers. C) Users can also choose a complement to the Almaya app: emulateme.ai. With uploaded information, we generate their Avatar that reflects how the person looks, sounds, and responds to almost any question. The Almaya app offers both individual and collaborative experiences, allowing families to engage together by recording their history and memories. Loved ones can access all digital content and engage in immersive conversations with the person through AI, anytime, anywhere. In the near future, we envision every family having an effortless way to interact with the essence of a departed relative, similar to how we interact with virtual assistants like Siri or Alexa. With Almaya, the wisdom and experiences of our loved ones endure, fostering connections that transcend time.

description: Protect your Social Media Brand using Artificial Intelligence
headquarters_regions: Europe, Middle East, and Africa (EMEA)
full_description: BrandFort (Brandfort.co) trained their Artificial Intelligence for understanding comments like a human does. BrandFort does not simply focus on certain keywords. No, BrandFort focuses on the meaning of a sentence and assess the sentiment of it. Based on this approach, BrandFort is able to detect sentences with a negative sentiment and complains in a efficient and effective manner. The same technology is used by BrandFort for detecting spam, profanity and hate. But, the big selling point of the software is to detect complains and negative sentiment in a very precise way. This is important if you are selling a product (or yourself) on your Social Media presence. Think about a comment like this one: "Oh my god, your product is so overpriced!" Normal content moderation, which is focused on detecting spam and profanity, will not hide such a comment. However, let's be honest, as a proud business owner, you do not want such a comment on your Facebook or Instagram page. BrandFort will detect such comments and hide it from your page. The smart thing, BrandFort will hide such a negative comment, but the commentator will not notice it. The commentator will see their comment on your Instagram page. But no one else will. Take your time responding to it and win the hater over. You can react to the negative comment in peace, but at the same time, you know it's not negatively impacting your brand reputation. BrandFort protects your brand 24/7, 365 days a year!

description: Cardinal is the system of record for product teams, allowing them to develop the correct items and fulfil data-driven goals.
headquarters_regions: Southern US
review_text:
Cardinal has single-handedly improved not only how our product team tracks the success of initiatives, but has also propelled our entire company to become more data-driven to guide decision-making. This is an immense culture shift that I do not believe would have happened in the same way without Cardinal. Integration of KPIs directly into product specifications has ensured that each new feature release is justified by existing metrics and its success is measured by the data changes that follow. My favorite feature dashboard, which has afforded our team the ability to have our metrics from Mixpanel, qualitative feedback from Typeform, and additional product specifications integrated into one clear space. This had become a crucially important component of my workflow as a designer and PM who is routinely needing to generate buy-in from other c-suite members to justify new initiatives. The dashboards aggregate everything into a digestible place that is easily presentable to other members of the team. I could continue to go on about the benefits that Cardinal has provided, but the best way to feel the impact is to experience, for yourself, how Cardinal takes your pre-existing product processes to the next level.

All in all, I'm immensely encouraged by what Cardinal has enabled for our team thus far and am even more ecstatic to see how much farther it will soar!

full_description: CodeWP is an AI-powered WordPress code generator designed for WordPress creators, capable of generating code for plugins, custom post types, WooCommerce, Oxygen, Breakdance, and Regex conditions. The tool covers PHP, JS, and several popular plugins, allowing users to create complex logic quickly and save time and money in developing snippets for WordPress websites. CodeWP is available in multiple languages and can be used by both non-techies and experienced developers, as it generates code snippets based on plain English inputs. The user-friendly tool is trained on millions of lines of WordPress code, with plugin-specific modes refined using code directly from plugin code bases. CodeWP's "modes" feature trains the AI for popular WordPress plugins like ACF, Elementor, WordPress SQL, Oxygen Builder, and more. For instance, the Oxygen Builder conditions AI mode was trained on numerous examples of conditions using the Conditions API. CodeWP aims to revolutionize the development process by providing on-demand code generation. By merely inputting a prompt, developers can harness the power of AI-driven code generation, making it a state-of-the-art tool built specifically for WordPress development. This innovative solution streamlines the workflow for both novice and expert developers, making it an invaluable asset in the world of WordPress creation.

From a marketing perspective, I was impressed by the marketing analytics dashboard. Dreams have fascinated humans for centuries, since they are portals to the subconscious mind and a canvas for the manifestation of our deepest desires, fears, and unresolved conflicts. Dream Interpreter AI offers an exciting opportunity to delve into the hidden meanings behind our nocturnal visions.

The tool is straightforward and user-friendly. It has an impressive understanding of symbolism, archetypes, and psychological elements. While it cannot replace the expertise of a professional human dream analyst, it provides valuable insights that can spark self-reflection and lead to a deeper understanding of one's psyche. However, sometimes, it does not fully connect the dots or provide detailed reasoning for its conclusions.

I use this tool daily and am looking forward to future product updates.

Use it to improve your mental health, achieve clarity about your goals and aspirations, or simply explore the mysteries of your subconscious mind. Whether you're seeking personal growth or simply curious about your dreams, DreamStory is the perfect tool to help you unlock the hidden meanings behind your subconscious mind. In summary, DreamStory is an AI-powered dream interpretation app that provides personalised insights into your subconscious mind. With features like daily dream logging, voice input, dream scoring, and personalised interpretations, DreamStory is the perfect tool for personal growth and insight. Whether you're looking to improve your mental health, achieve clarity about your goals and aspirations, or simply explore the mysteries of your subconscious mind, DreamStory has everything you need to get started.

description: Durable is an online platform that assists service businesses with the setup, templates, marketing, and invoicing of their company.
headquarters_regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
full_description: Durable is an online platform that assists service businesses with the setup, templates, marketing, and invoicing of their company. The platform is enabling millions of people worldwide to escape the labor trap and build their own businesses. Its mission is to make starting a solo business easier than working for someone else. Durable was founded in 2021 and is based in San Francisco, California.
review_text:
I have so many questions and concerns about this "website builder." However, before delving into them, I must caution against relying on this tool for any important purposes, especially if you are considering using it for business. The reason being that you will not have ownership of your website, as you are unable to copy or export the code. The CRM is a nice feature; however, my suggestion is that if you have to choose, it would be better to invest in your website, spend the money on branding, and design so that customers will remember and admire you and using an Excel spreadsheet to keep track of your client information. This way, in the event that this company goes out of business, you will not lose your website as you will have ownership of the code.

The strangest aspect of this business model is the many roles that the owner is attempting to play. Durable is asking users to either buy insurance from them or disclose information about their current insurance policies. However, Durable has not provided any explanation as to why they need access to users' financial information, nor is there any evidence to support their legal authority to conduct insurance business. Additionally, Durable would like to be your money manager, but it is unclear why Durable is qualified to act as a money manager for your business, as they have not provided any credentials or meaningful information on their expertise in this area. It seems that Durable wants to have control over every aspect of your life, business, and finances, manage your money, and in return, you will have no ownership. The creator's approach to launching a business website is unusual, and I strongly advise against sharing any personal information or giving them money. Please review their terms of service, which specifically state that they will own your website and that they can change the terms of service at any time. Check Crunchbase to see that this company was formed in 2021 and is in the early stages of financing with an investment firm. Please do not be deceived into thinking that you will have any legal recourse if this is not what it appears to be or if the owners decide to pivot their business strategy and leave you with nothing.

Edit: I have one more thing to say. It is troubling that Durable focuses on attracting very tiny, startup companies. It's important to keep in mind that they will never truly own the site, despite the fact that some business owners, such as dog walkers, artists, and daycare center owners, may see it as a way to avoid the perceived hassle of establishing a website. They will always be reliant on Durable, and they will have to continue making payments to keep the site up and running or risk losing it altogether. If you're a small business owner seeking a risk-free option to quickly and easily build a website, Google Business is worth considering, but you *must* learn how to customize your website for SEO or search engines will never find you. Google Business is a free platform with drag-and-drop customization options. Additionally, if you ever decide to switch platforms, you can use the takeout feature to download your website and take it with you. You might need up to a week to build it, but isn't it worth it? Although it doesn't seem as magical as this product, you won't run the chance of losing your website. To begin, create a company profile and follow the guided setup process. You can use the available tools and templates to build a website that reflects your brand's identity and even add code for further customization, if desired. Although you may want to think about hiring an expert in the future, Google Business is a great way to build your online presence quickly and for no cost. Try it out. You've got this!

review_text:
Dan, the experience is amazing actually. It seem that saving lots of time. But I'm curious about that what's different between Using ChatGPT directly and User Persona Generator?

Here is the prompt,

```
I want to open a all-natural bubble tea shop, targeting stressed-out working professionals.

Please help me create a hypothetical User Persona, with a defined user background.

Problem:
Your Persona is grappling with this challenge.

Pains:
And particularly facing these adverse outcomes.

Goal:
Your Persona aims to attain this transformation.

Benefit:
So they can enjoy these favorable results.

Trigger:
This incident compelled your Persona to seek a solution.

Barriers:
However, these uncertainties hinder your Persona's progress.
```

And the result

```
**User Persona: Stressed-Out Sarah**

**Background:**
Sarah is a 32-year-old working professional who lives in a bustling urban area. She works as a project manager in a fast-paced tech company, where long hours, tight deadlines, and constant pressure are the norms. Her job demands not only her physical presence but also her mental energy. Sarah is highly dedicated to her work, often sacrificing her personal time to ensure her projects succeed. This lifestyle has started taking a toll on her well-being.

**Problem:**
Sarah is grappling with chronic stress and burnout due to her demanding job. She often feels overwhelmed, drained, and mentally exhausted. The work-related stress has started affecting her sleep, mood, and overall quality of life. She is searching for healthy ways to manage her stress and find moments of relaxation in her busy schedule.

**Pains:**
1. **Physical Exhaustion:** Sarah experiences frequent headaches, muscle tension, and fatigue due to prolonged periods of stress.
2. **Poor Sleep:** Her stress levels make it difficult for her to fall asleep and stay asleep through the night.
3. **Lack of Relaxation:** She struggles to find moments of tranquility during her hectic workdays.
4. **Decreased Concentration:** The constant stress has led to difficulty in focusing on tasks and making decisions.
5. **Social Isolation:** Sarah's busy work life leaves her with limited time to socialize or engage in hobbies, resulting in feelings of isolation.

**Goal:**
Sarah aims to attain a healthier work-life balance and manage her stress more effectively. She wants to incorporate relaxation and self-care practices into her routine to improve her overall well-being. Her ultimate goal is to find a way to unwind during her workdays and regain her sense of calm.

**Benefit:**
By achieving her goals, Sarah will:
1. Experience reduced stress and burnout, leading to improved mental and physical health.
2. Enjoy better sleep quality, allowing her to wake up refreshed and energized.
3. Enhance her concentration and decision-making abilities, leading to increased productivity at work.
4. Create opportunities for social interaction and personal hobbies, reducing feelings of isolation.

**Trigger:**
Sarah's turning point came when she experienced a panic attack during a particularly stressful presentation at work. This incident made her realize the urgent need to address her stress levels and prioritize her well-being.

**Barriers:**
1. **Time Constraints:** Sarah's demanding job often leaves her with limited time to invest in self-care activities.
2. **Skepticism:** She may be skeptical about the effectiveness of new relaxation methods, given her busy lifestyle.
3. **Work Culture:** The prevailing culture at her workplace might not encourage taking breaks or focusing on well-being during work hours.
4. **Lack of Knowledge:** Sarah might not be aware of the various options available to manage stress and find relaxation in her daily routine.

Understanding the challenges and aspirations of Stressed-Out Sarah will help you tailor your all-natural bubble tea shop to meet her needs. Your shop could provide her with a soothing and rejuvenating environment where she can take short breaks, enjoy healthy bubble tea options, and find moments of tranquility amidst her busy workdays.
```

review_text:
I recently had the chance to check out Covey Scout, an AI assistant built specifically for recruiters, and wow, I'm seriously impressed! This app is a game-changer for anyone in the recruiting industry who wants to find and engage candidates with human-level accuracy and a straightforward user interface.

Covey Scout stands out from other recruiting tools with its sophisticated AI algorithms that analyze and understand job descriptions, candidate profiles, and company culture to identify the most suitable candidates for any given role. It's amazing how accurate it is!

What I appreciate about Covey Scout is its user interface - it's clean, simple, and refreshingly easy to use. Even if you're not a tech whiz, the app's intuitive interface makes it a breeze to navigate.

Another excellent feature of Covey Scout is its ability to automate communication with potential candidates, which saves recruiters time and keeps candidates informed and engaged throughout the recruitment process. This is a major plus, as it can help increase the likelihood of finding the ideal candidate for any given role.

In a nutshell, Covey Scout is an AI assistant that can help recruiters find and engage candidates with impressive accuracy, all through a refreshingly user-friendly interface. Its advanced algorithms analyze job descriptions, candidate profiles, and company culture to identify the best possible matches for any given role, and its automation features help recruiters save time and stay on top of their recruitment processes. For recruiters looking to increase their efficiency and productivity, Covey Scout is a must-try tool.

Hey Sayoni, Kshitiz, and the Gist AI team! üéâ

First off, congrats on the Product Hunt launch! That's a big step, and it's totally okay to be a mix of thrilled and nervous. Been there, felt that!

Now, about Gist AI. I'm vibing with the problem you're solving. Summarization tools can be a hit or miss, and you've nailed the issues most of us face. The "Read More" feature? Genius! It's like having a 'skip intro' button but for content. ü§Ø

The unlimited, unrestricted summaries are a big win, especially for those of us who devour content like it's our job (because sometimes, it is). And let's not forget the language barrier you're smashing with the 30+ language translations. üåç

Kshitiz, your excitement about summarizing long PDFs for free is contagious. I mean, who wouldn't want that? üìö

A couple of things to ponder:

How does Gist AI handle super technical or niche content?
Any plans for mobile support?
Your tool sounds like a game-changer, and I'm stoked to see how it evolves. Keep crushing it, and best of luck! üöÄ

Cheers! ü•Ç

review_text: My experience has been flawless so far. The interface is just so intuitive that the learning curve was almost non-existant. Aside of the direct utility of the app, it's an amazing way of getting introduced to the world of AI and explore it's possibilities. This is basicly bringing AI to the rest of the world! Keep it up!

The resulting prompt is pretty accurate. I have tried with two versions of the same photo, one with its original background and one without it (transparent) and I received two different meaningful prompts accordingly. The pricing is a bit off, in my opinion: it makes the top tier the best option but that might discourage the occasional user because they might never be using 500 prompts while the entry tier at 20 cents per prompt seems a bit overpriced in comparison. The "issue" with AI images is that the generated photos are still far away from usable in a professional environment and several tries and fine-tuning are required before getting a decent result; this app certainly create good prompts and it has room for improvements but ultimately its value will increase in time when AI generated images will also get better. To me in order to keep that pricing model additional features need to be added. For example, if it generates the prompt, why not offering also the change to use it on site to generate the next photo? Or why not transforming it into an API that can be integrated with existing AI image generators? Just my idea, of course.

One thing I'd definitely consider adding though is suggesting aperture, focus and other tech camera settings, when user upload a real photo. I don't know how the system works in the background, hence if this is easily implementable or not, but in order to get a realistic photo back from an AI generator, those parameters and especially the correct ones are paramount.

All in all, this has potential and it is well crafted so considering that this is a first launch, I definitely support it.
Thumbs up for this AI product and their exceptional support. They truly go the extra mile.

description: GhostCut is an AI video editing tool.It provides auto video inpainting/auto translation and dubbing/auto hard sub translation...
full_description: Founded in 2019, JollyToday Technology is a SAAS company focusing on global video e-commerce. GhostCut is an intelligent video editing software builded by JollyToday. Its core purpose is to help customers improve the processing speed of materials and the quality of video creativity. We have used a lot of AI capabilities in various audio and video processing details to improve the processing efficiency of videos. GhostCut provide some amazing features: 1.Video Text auto RemovalÔºöAutomatically detect all text/subtitles in the video through OCR and perform video inpainting to restore the erased video parts as much as possible; 2.Video Text Auto TranslationÔºöAutomatically detect the text/subtitles in the video through OCR, calculate and extract text position, style, size in the video, and then use ChatGPT to translate the subtitles and paste them back according to the original text style and position, while performing inpainting on the original text area; 3.Video Voice Auto Translation and dubbingÔºö Automatically extract the voice in the video through ASR and translate it, while using TTS to synthesize the translated text into voice. In this process, the position of the original picture, voice, and subtitles is calculated, and the newly synthesized voice, subtitles, and original picture are automatically aligned to ensure the consistency of sound and picture. You can choose whether to perform inpainting smudging on the original text and whether to retain the original sound. The effect of retaining the original sound is to automatically separate the human voice and background music of the original video and retain the background music. 4.Auto Video DeduplicationÔºö Automatically make minor modifications to the video, and automatically complete the following operations, including but not limited to modifying md5, removing video fingerprints, superimposing picture-in-picture in the video, minor cropping, using Gaussian blur, automatic cover clipping, slightly tilting the picture, using sharpening, using acceleration and deceleration, and other transitions, filters, scaling, etc. Generally used for quick secondary creation for short video....

description: Landbot.io is a no-code chatbot platform that empowers businesses to build frictionless conversational experiences from end-to-end.
headquarters_regions: European Union (EU), Europe, Middle East, and Africa (EMEA)
full_description: Landbot.io is a no-code chatbot platform that empowers businesses to build frictionless conversational experiences from end-to-end.  Turning conversations into profitable outcomes, Landbot helps Marketing, Operations, and Customer Service teams triple their efficiency and cut operating costs by 30% or more. Whether it's for WhatsApp, Web, or Messenger, anyone can create automated chatbot flows to better engage customers and increase conversion rates.  Landbot is also leveraging recent advancements in AI and ChatGPT to help make the chatbot building experience even more accessible, combining the no-code capabilities of Landbot with other Large Language Models.
review_text:
Brilliant product, excited to see where it goes. Fun to use if you enjoy trying to create engaging and human conversational flows. *nerd alert*

Two things I don't love: 1. Needs work for our mobile visitors. Looks zoomed out and far from optimal for a mobile visitor, a bad experience on this is worse than no experience at all, so a bit of a showstopper for me at the moment, for risk of providing a bad experience (no way of tracking or following this experience to check it's going smooth for mobile visitors, so a tiny risk to go live with if have lots of visitors on mobile)

Secondly, at the end of every flow on the freemium a "share this Landbot" button appears alongside a CTA to create their own. Obviously, I get it, it's a free product, do what you want. If I want to remove that, I can pay to do so. Just my personal opinion, and more feedback than a request, is that I think it's a bad time to "Hijack" MY visitors attention to market YOUR product at what is often for these forms, the critical moment, the end. They're at a decision crossroads. We've just exchanged information, i've taken them on this journey, and then BAM, you come and sweep them off their feet and they forget all the sweet nothings they and i whispered to each other.

My only point is, IF others have this gripe too, they might leave and not give the product a chance to become part of their paid stack, instead of upgrading straight away to remove this barrier to them. If this barrier didn't exist, (your branding is still on the page top right anyway), they may implement, become an active user, and give you plenty of time to convert them to a paid plan as you continue to execute and improve the product from now on out.

Keep up the great work.

description: AI-powered contextual computer vision ad platform
headquarters_regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
full_description: LensAI is an AI-powered contextual computer vision ad solution that monetizes any visual content and fine-tunes targeting through identifying objects, logos, actions, and context and matching them with relevant ads. The core of LensAI Technology is associative thinking AI algorithm that, when applied to the digital advertising industry, automatically selects and embeds relevant ads into any content consumed by users in real-time. LensAI prioritizes first-party relationships and targets audiences based on the content they are interested in and drawn to, not personal information about users. LensAI does not depend on cookies or alternative user-level identifiers while enabling Advertisers to reach relevant audiences by tailoring ads to the context. As users have become very particular about the kind of ads they want to see, LensAI focuses on providing value with every ad. To make it more fun, LensAI's in-image and in-video ads look like shopping hints that users may have seen in video games rather than traditional ads. The analytics engine of the LensAI technology measures how every ad performs contextually and how different contexts perform against each other and in general. LensAI takes digital advertising to a new level with value, relevance and no privacy hackles.

full_description: Microsoft is an American multinational corporation that develops, manufactures, licenses, supports, and sells a range of software products and services. Microsoft‚Äôs devices and consumer (D&C) licensing segment licenses the Windows operating system and related software, Microsoft Office for consumers, and the Windows Phone operating system. The company‚Äôs computing and gaming hardware segment provides Xbox gaming and entertainment consoles and accessories, second-party and third-party video games, and Xbox Live subscriptions; surface devices and accessories; and Microsoft PC accessories. Its phone hardware segment offers Lumia smartphones and other non-Lumia phones. Its D&C segment provides Windows Store, Xbox Live transactions, and Windows phone store; search advertising; display advertising; Office 365 Home and Office 365 Personal; first-party video games; and other consumer products and services as well as operating retail stores. Microsoft‚Äôs commercial licensing segments license server products, including Windows Server, Microsoft SQL Server, Visual Studio, System Center, and related Client Access Licenses (CALs); Windows Embedded; Windows operating system; Microsoft Office for business, including Office, Exchange, SharePoint, Lync, and related CALs; Microsoft Dynamics business solutions; and Skype. Its commercial segment offers enterprise services, including premier support services and Microsoft consulting services; commercial cloud comprising Office 365 Commercial, other Microsoft Office online offerings, Dynamics CRM Online, and Microsoft Azure; and other commercial products and online services. The company markets and distributes its products through original equipment manufacturers, distributors, and resellers, as well as online.

description: Max Planck Society (with its 86 Max Planck Institutes) is widely regarded as one of the foremost basic research organizations in the world.
headquarters_regions: European Union (EU), Europe, Middle East, and Africa (EMEA)
full_description: The Max Planck Society for the Advancement of Science (German: Max-Planck-Gesellschaft zur F√∂rderung der Wissenschaften e. V.; abbreviated MPG) is a non-governmental and non-profit association of Research Institutes publicly funded by the federal and the state governments of Germany. Additionally, the Max Planck Society and its Institutes receive third party funding from public and private contributions and from the European Union. The world leading organization is named in honor of its former president, theoretical physicist Max Planck. The 86 Institutes and Research Facilities of the Max Planck Society (as of 2020) conduct basic research in the natural sciences, life sciences, social sciences, and the arts and humanities. They have a total staff of approximately 24,000 permanent employees, including 15,000 scientists, and around 5,000 non-tenured scientists and guests. As of December 31, 2018, the proportion of female employees was 44.4 percent. The Max Planck Society (with its 86 Max Planck Institutes) has a world-leading reputation as a science and technology research organization, with more than 33 Nobel Prizes awarded to its scientists, and is widely regarded as one of the foremost basic research organizations in the world.

description: AI-driven news aggregator that analyzes the news using natural language processing to empower readers in identifying news media influence.
headquarters_regions: Greater Miami Area, East Coast, Southern US
full_description: NOOZ.AI provides the following: ARTICLE ANALYSIS: Get visual insight into media bias via labels for opinion, sentiment, propaganda, revisions, and ghost edits on each news listing. OPINION ANALYSIS: Discover how much a journalist expresses personal feelings, views, or judgments regarding the story‚Äôs topic. Opinion scores are grouped into 5 opinion labels: Neutral, Slight, Partial, High, and Extreme. SENTIMENT ANALYSIS: Gauge the journalist‚Äôs positivity (sympathy & support) or negativity (antagonism & opposition) concerning the story‚Äôs topic. Sentiment scores are grouped into 5 sentiment labels: Very Negative, Negative, Neutral, Positive, and Very Positive. PROPAGANDA ANALYSIS: Detect potential disinformation by identifying the usage of up to 18 possible persuasion techniques. Some of the more common types of propaganda found are ‚ÄúFlag Waving‚Äù, ‚ÄúName Calling, Labeling‚Äù, ‚ÄúExaggeration, Minimization‚Äù, ‚ÄúAppeal to Fear & Prejudice‚Äù, and ‚ÄúLoaded Language‚Äù, just to name a few. REVISION ANALYSIS: Investigate the evolution of a news story and the writer‚Äôs manipulation of opinion, sentiment, and propaganda over time. Our analytics reveal all the changes in each published revision of a specific news article and identifies ‚Äúghost edits‚Äù that occur when the publisher does not update the published date after making a change.

review_text:
I've been using PicSo for over a week now, and honestly, it's easily the easiest and easiest AI painting app I've come across. If you aspire to create AI art but are put off by the steep learning curve or cost of tools in the industry (like midjourney), then PicSo is really for you! It supports web and client use, anyone can easily get started, and use the unique prompt to instantly create beautiful AI artworks.
PicSo is comparable to any AI Text to Art program, has beautiful builds, and the ability to choose how many images are produced each time is an amazing feature. In addition to the styles they provide, you can also enter your desired styles and effects in the prompt. You can enter a piece of text like I do:
messy steampunk Interior of an observatory, Blue light, Telescope, Shelves of geode and cyystals and glass jars and moss, Cluttered with Star maps, charts and tools, Dramatic lighting, Epic composition, Wide angle, by Miyazaki, Nausicaa Ghibli, Breath of The Wild

Then choose to generate 9 pictures at a time;
After a few seconds, you will have 9 Masterpieces!

This is an amazing support development team!

Pros:
- Free trial!
- Easy to learn and very user friendly
- Short production time
- Nice tool for design or other purposes
- Everything is always saved in the cloud, and history is automatically saved
- Both available on web and APP Store
- Interesting Discovery community

Cons:
- The length of the prompt is limited in 300-character .


PicSo is literally giving everyone a chance to try these AI techs and I can't wait to see what the future holds!

description: PimEyes is an advanced face recognition search engine, a reverse image search tool, and a photo search mechanism.
headquarters_regions: Europe, Middle East, and Africa (EMEA)
full_description: PimEyes is an online search engine that looks for the web sites based on photos submitted by the users. PimEyes doesn‚Äôt look for people, it looks for the web sites. PimEyes doesn‚Äôt label any picture based on race, gender, age, or any other feature necessary to identify an individual. Gathering information on individuals is not the goal of the search engine, neither it is designed to do so. The engine gathers information about the URL addresses openly available on the internet. PimEyes searches for an opened internet and gathers information which is public, not restricted by user, or owner and everyone has right to see it. The database itself consists of coded indexes, where each code is indicating a certain feature. The index is linked to the web site, where photo material with similar index is published. Accordingly, PimEyes database is a puzzle and the photo provided by the user is a key to the puzzle. Database is technically structured in a manner that the puzzle solving is available only with PimEyes‚Äô unique AI. It is technically and theoretically impossible to reconstruct a single image even in case a leak of the entire database. PimEyes database is not designed to reconstruct images inside a database. Once the photo is submitted the AI calculates index combination provided by the photo and provides the URL addresses from the database which include those combinations with bigger similarity. Accordingly, users are provided data from the database, however images are displayed from the external sources. PimEyes doesn‚Äôt keep the photos used or published by the various websites.

review_text:
Interesting and useful tool. I work with content a lot and we started using chat GPT recently as it saves a lot of time when generating templated articles. However, the news that Google will crack down AI content are not great. We constantly need to check our writers' content and make sure it's not purely AI-written (though we allow 80%+ human-written texts).

This software has an option to upload a document, which not many services have. Also it highlights the pieces that look like AI-generated, which is convenient for writers and editors, there's no need in guessing and rewriting everything.

Room for improvement: make it possible to edit the text inside the field once you've checked it. It saves time to not go back to the original document and look for words and phrases to edit them and then copy to the detector again.

Overall, quite a useful service, can recommend to all content creators and managers

review_text:
I've bought a lot of tools but it's been a while since I left a review.

Re:tune definitely deserves a shout. I've recently been given inspiration on a few things and long story short, knew that I would need an easily trainable AI chatbot to achieve certain goals.

Lo and behold, Re:tune appears just at the right time! I tried a few other AI chatbot builders but 1) the limits sucked and 2) they weren't as easy to setup.

I had a fully trained and deployed, niche AI chatbot within 10 minutes using Re:tune. There was a hiccup with some AI delusions but Dhanajoy and the team fixed this in no time by adding the Restrictions feature - spot on!

Now my chatbots are literally on point and firing on all virtual cylinders. I'm VERY much looking forward to the lead capture feature (ideally with Webhooks) so I can grab interested customers details at the right time.

They've recently release Capture, which can ask for any type of data you want to gather from the customer. This is a game changer.

For me, this is a platform to watch. My requests:
1. Have a developed integration marketplace, i.e. send chats to Google Sheets (upcoming webhooks / Zapier integrations will help with this)
2. Notifications - Notify on app when a keyword/lead is entered and handover to human (handover on roadmap I believe) or even send email
3. More automation capabilities. E.g. Run scheduled crawls of Google Drive folder/URL and pick up pdfs/website URLs automatically so to keep knowledge updated automatically (this is on the roadmap)

DJ asked on their Discord, but I can definitely see Re:tune as a leader in this space in 5 years of staying on current course. The ability for any non-coding entrepreneur to put a wealth of knowledge on a website within minutes is truly awesome. Thank you for helping me (and countless others) reach the next stage of my evolution!

review_text:
Interesting idea and execution thus far is impressive!

I have one question regarding privacy.

>. For your privacy, we store all of the recordings locally on your Mac. Only you have access to them. Compression and Automated Speech Recognition (ASR) is all done locally. Recording data is never sent off of your machine.

Although recording data might not be sent off the machine, usage of GPT-4 does imply you're sending sensitive data to OpenAI (and thus off the machine).

Presumably you're embedding user's screen and audio data locally, which means that potentially the embedding process and definitely the response generation process both send data to OpenAI, which is a privacy concern.

Do you plan on implement on-device models in the future, as way to mitigate this?

full_description: Rose is a next-generation data management platform that allows users to quickly find relevant data and interact with it in a way that allows them to make data driven decisions.  Dealing with large amounts of data is a painful experience.  The world is fifty odd years into the information revolution, and yet even the most sophisticated of institutions are still working on data using the same hodgepodge of opaque databases and error-prone spreadsheets developed decades ago.   Finding what you want is difficult, cleaning data is a constant pain, and integrating information across sources and tools requires investing huge amounts of time and human capital.  Rose addresses these issues by providing you with a hub for finding, cleaning, and interacting with your data.  Rose's data marketplace gives users exposure to a wide array of robust data sets from a myriad of reputable providers. Users can view how a dataset is constructed and can pull the underlying data into an Excel spreadsheet or Jupyter Notebook.  Information is the most valuable commodity in the marketplace today. Rose gives your organization a common set of tools for manipulating, sharing, and profiting off the backbreaking work of turning raw information into insights that drive decisions.

description: Rythmex is an AI-powered Speech-to-Text transcription solution
headquarters_regions: Europe, Middle East, and Africa (EMEA)
full_description: Rythmex is an AI-powered Speech-to-Text transcription solution revolutionizing the way businesses transcribe their audio and video recordings. From the very beginning, we are aiming to become a high-en solution for mid-size and enterprise companies. That‚Äôs why we keep improving Rythmex making it the best transcription software on the market. Features: - Automatic language identification with 140 languages and accents which is currently recognizable by Rythmex - In-built editor with automatic punctuation & number normalization - Custom Vocabulary. Add specific words and phrases to your own custom dictionary. This will help to get top-level accuracy transcription accuracy. - Medical Transcription. Allows transcribing medical conversations with a HIPAA-eligible automatic speech recognition service. - Recognize multiple speakers (up to 4 in one conversation) & Channel identification (transcribing multi-channel audio) - Rythmex Call Analytics. This feature is designed to provide detailed post-call analytics. With this, customers will not only transcribe calls automatically but also gain detailed insights into the operator and the client sentiment, non-speak durations, operator performance and file information. Call Analytics would also summarize the transcribed file and provide you with feedback on the issue of the call, and what was the proposed way of solving the problem provided by the operator. - AI Summarization. This high-end feature provides our customers with the ability to get a quick summary of the transcribed file. This will Maximize your productivity and save time. - Subtitles Generator. Makes it easy for companies to add subtitles to their on-demand content with no prior ML experience required. - Team management. Full control over the team - track credits usage and collaborate on files together - API access. Integrate Rythmex into any system to perform automatic transcription tasks. - Account analytics. Track and Analyse your credit spending, and download invoices. For Whom: –°all center or dispatch service. By using Rythmex, the customer support service can generate transcripts from a call recordings, which can be used for training or quality control purposes. It can help analyze customer satisfaction, understand common problems, and provide training materials for new support staff. Tech Companies: Transcription solutions can be incorporated into products or services that involve voice recognition, like virtual assistants or transcription software itself. Healthcare Organizations: Hospitals, clinics, and research organizations use transcription services for medical records, patient consultations, research notes, interviews and incoming calls. This helps maintain patient records and aids in the review and analysis of medical data. Financial Institutions: Transcriptions of earnings calls, meetings, and analyst interviews can be crucial for record-keeping and decision-making processes. Government Agencies: Transcription services can be used for public hearings, investigations, press briefings, and other forms of official communication. Legal Firms and Departments: They require transcription services for legal proceedings, depositions, and client consultations. These transcriptions can help them maintain accurate records, increase efficiency, and support case preparation. Human Resources Departments: Transcription can be useful during interviews, disciplinary hearings, and training sessions, helping to keep a clear record of these events. Media and Entertainment Industry: They need transcription services for scripts, interviews, broadcasts, and subtitles. This aids in content creation, post-production processes, and accessibility requirements. Market Research Companies: These companies use transcription services to transcribe focus groups, interviews, and surveys. The transcripts can help them analyze and interpret the data more effectively.

review_text:
I can see myself using this for side projects. Onboarding is clear and fast and task completion is a breeze as well. UI is friendly, except for the FRAMES section on the left, when I create a post: personally I wasn't able to understand what their function is because their imagery seemed unrelated with my post and when I clicked on few of them they seemed to get selected but nothing happened. They must have a function, and I always have a super dummy approach when I try and review new apps so maybe you could try to improve the informational side of what does what. Just my 2 cents, of course.

Personally, I would also add a publish button to post making window/draft, maybe beside PREVIEW. Right now it seems to be only available from the 3 dots on the CONTENT page. It makes perfect sense, don't misunderstand me, but whenever one step can be saved I'd always go for that.

All the above don't affect my rating because it is expected to have terrain for improvement at launch, especially when it comes to UI and documentation.

The issue I have is with AI-powered imagery: that technology is still far away from being usable in apps like this, because the results are awful. Those of Stori AI are not even that bad, but still not viable for branding, in my opinion. Thing is that this is a common problem to all similar apps right now, so I don't feel like it is a flaw of this particular app. My suggestion to anybody offering this kind of tech in an automated way as a feature of their app is to always "sell it" as a beta feature while offering in-app editing tools for real imagery as the selling point, because AI-powered imagery doesn't meet customers' expectations yet.

About AI-powered text, to the contrary, there's really good prompting behind this app, and with a bit of manual editing here and there one can really save time and money. That makes it a worthy app with great potential, to me; one that I will use for some of my side projects, and whose evolution I'll certainly keep an eye on. üëÄ

Definitely supporting it.
So cool project :) my son love it

description: StoryFile is an information technology company that develops storytelling application to distribute stories and voices globally.
headquarters_regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
full_description: StoryFile is changing the way people interact and communicate with each other and the world. Through user-led voice-activated technology, advanced AI and beyond, StoryFile provides a platform for an intimate and natural conversational video interactive experience. StoryFile is a content-driven technology company that allows individuals to preserve, share, and consume stories and experiences through its proprietary and innovative legacy capture system.   StoryFile is reimagining storytelling by authentically preserving memories, moments, and beyond, in a meaningful way that empowers the storyteller and user. By preserving stories and history in a way that allows users to have authentic interactions, StoryFile is not only creating a new form of storytelling, but is also creating more sustainable bonds between people, everywhere.   Creating a world where everyone, anywhere, anytime, can connect with those living or in the past is finally a reality with StoryFile.  This visual and interactive storytelling platform allows people to have a natural conversation across time and space.   Just think ‚Äì StoryFile gives your great-great grandchildren an opportunity to speak with you, learn from you, and get to know you in a way that was never possible before. The gift of storytelling ‚Äì the gift of passing experiences to future generations ‚Äì is priceless. StoryFile wants to ensure each and every person has such opportunity ‚Äì from the Studio experience to the app, there is something for everyone!   Here‚Äôs how it works: An individual is filmed (or films themselves) answering questions about their life, which are then processed and stored on the StoryFile platform. Users can then have a real life-like conversation with the filmed-version of the individual on the web or mobile application ‚Äì anytime, anywhere. StoryFile‚Äôs platform promotes user-led education and curiosity, providing an opportunity for users to directly engage with the interviewee. StoryFile captures the interviewee‚Äôs legacy in a unique way by empowering the interviewee to pass on their values, struggles, life lessons, morals, decisions and more, while inspiring future generations.   About The StoryFile Experience: The StoryFile experience is intimate, personal and truly unique. StoryFile has created a warm and comfortable studio space for the interviewee to share his/her life lessons, personal memories, struggles, triumphs, joys, milestones, and more. The most important thing about you is your story, so it‚Äôs the most important story to tell. StoryFile‚Äôs team takes the time to get to know you, and works with you and your family to craft and facilitate the telling of that story, as it is the most important gift to future generations you will ever give. StoryFile‚Äôs studio is equipped with cutting edge technology that produces 3D assets as well as Hi-Fidelity 2D images. This is how the magic is made.

description: Infrastructure to build, manage & run useful autonomous AI agents
headquarters_regions: Greater Philadelphia Area, East Coast, Southern US
full_description: Open-source framework for developers designed to Build, deploy, and manage Autonomous AI Agents. Features include: - Agent provisioning and execution offer the ability to run multiple agents concurrently for maximum efficiency. Developers can expand these agents' capabilities by using a growing library of tools or by creating custom tools tailored to their needs. - The platform includes a graphical user interface (GUI) for easy management and interaction with agents. For direct input and permissions management, an action console is provided. SuperAGI supports multiple Vector DB connections, which improves agent performance and data access. - Create multi-model agents that can be tailored to specific tasks. This is enhanced further by agent trajectory fine-tuning, in which agents learn and optimise their performance via feedback loops. - Performance telemetry provides useful insights into agent performance, allowing for optimisation and improvement. The platform also emphasises effective token management, balancing the costs associated with its use. - SuperAGI enables agents to store their experiences, thereby facilitating continuous learning and adaptation. To prevent looping issues, it employs looping detection heuristics that notify developers when an agent is stuck, enabling proactive resolution. - A resource manager is included for the handling of files generated by agents, ensuring efficient data management and analysis.

headquarters_regions: European Union (EU), Europe, Middle East, and Africa (EMEA)
full_description: Syntho is a data technology organization with a strong expertise in privacy enhancing technologies (PET), headquartered in Amsterdam, Netherlands. It was founded in 2020 with the goal of solving the privacy dilemma and enable the open data economy, where data can be used and shared freely and privacy guaranteed. Syntho offers privacy-preserving synthetic data to unlock your data and take away legitimate privacy concerns. We develop AI-based software that can be trained on any form of data. After training, our Syntho Engine is able to generate new, ‚Äòsynthetic‚Äô data. This is the essence of what we do - we generate a completely new, artificial dataset that reproduces the statistical characteristics of the original dataset, while warranting that no records from the original dataset are present. In other words, the synthetic dataset has no privacy risk, while maximizing data utility. This allows you to easily use and share all of your data without privacy concerns and boost innovation.

description: Unlearn.AI combines AI, digital twins, and novel statistical methods to enable smaller, more efficient clinical trials.
headquarters_regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
full_description: Unlearn.AI is a biotech AI company that develops a digital twin service for clinical trials. Digital twins enhance¬†healthcare by assessing health risks before a disease manifests its symptoms, according to some experts.¬† Unlearn brings together a world-class team of experts across pharma, medtech, machine learning, and business who share a vision of using machine learning and biostatistics to improve clinical trials for the benefit of patients and sponsors. Unlearn invented their TwinRCT solution to enable biopharma partners to run faster, more successful clinical trials. A TwinRCT is a randomized trial that uses machine learning to achieve a higher probability of success with a smaller number of patients. As in a traditional RCT, patients are randomized to a treatment group and a control group, but, unlike a traditional trial, a prognostic digital twin is created for every patient using a machine learning model trained on historical data. The treatment effects for the primary and secondary outcomes can all be estimated from the trial with greater precision after correcting for a prognostic score derived for each patient's digital twin. TwinRCTs provide a scientifically-sound method for using deep learning and historical patient data to improve clinical trials.

description: Generative Search for Secure Data
headquarters_regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
full_description: Meru is out-of-the-box generative search that runs only where you want it to, with zero external data transfer. We're cloud-agnostic, compute-agnostic (CPU/GPU) and always compliant.  With Meru you can deploy a full stack generative search product as a container on any infrastructure. Meru containers come preloaded with a custom base large language model, embeddings model, vector store, and an intelligent, custom-designed retrieval function.  Meru can run on air gapped systems, which means your data is never sent over the internet, ever.  Meru is not a 'third party'. It is a software package you download, deploy, and control in its entirety. This means you have full visibility into your data pipeline, and can remain compliant without negotiating any service agreements.  Meru is fully extensible. You have the freedom to build custom ETL, analytics, and more around our containers to fully meet your needs.  Meru saves you money. Instead of relying on strict volume-based pricing from third-party APIs, Meru allows you to control your costs by choosing which instances to deploy on (including CPU deployments) and scaling up and down according to demand.  Meru is reliable. You launch Meru on your own infrastructure, which means no need to worry about rate limits, API downtime, and variable latency.

Outstanding WhatsApp transcription service - Whisperbot exceeds all expectations!
I was looking for a good transcription service for WhatsApp, and most I had tried were pretty disappointing until I came across Whisperbot. It converts spoken text into written text with exceptional accuracy. It opens up new possibilities for working with spoken content.
The first thing that struck me was how well Whisperbot could accurately convert spoken text. Even with complex sentences and different speaking styles, it managed to convey the meaning precisely. This has opened up new possibilities for me to work with spoken content, as I can now use the transcriptions for reference, notes or even for creating articles. It really is a great tool for anyone dealing with a significant amount of spoken text.
What makes Whisperbot even more appealing is its ease of use. The interface is intuitive and user-friendly, and I was able to get up and running quickly without any technical difficulties. The process is simple: you just upload the audio file with the spoken text and the service takes care of the rest. Moreover, the processing time is also impressive. I never had to wait long to receive my transcriptions, which significantly sped up my workflow.
Another aspect I really appreciate about Whisperbot is the accuracy of the transcriptions. I have used other transcription services that often struggled to correctly identify words and sentence structures, resulting in errors and ambiguities. review_text:
Update July 2023

I have been working with Writers brew AI for several months now and I want to emphasize the significant increase in efficiency that this application has brought to my daily work routine. Professionally, I regularly have to write emails and texts that should meet a certain minimum quality.

In the past, I often experienced writer's block and would leave things untouched for days until I was in the right mood to write the texts. With Writers brew AI, I can now simply jot down the text as it comes to mind. Afterwards, Writers brew AI immediately provides me with a polished, refined, and perfectly formulated version of the text that is also grammatically correct.

Moreover, writing texts is now incredibly fun. In the past, I often squeezed the last bit of brain out of me with force, with a lot of coffee and a lot of time, to write a good text. Now I write anything, no matter how I feel, and Writersbrew perfects it.

I could achieve something similar with Chat-GPT, of course. Some texts might even improve further if I could use GPT 4, but I don't have access to the API for that. Therefore, I exclusively use Writers brew AI with GPT 3.5. Nevertheless, I only work with Writers brew AI because it is possible to improve the text immediately. Writers Brew also has the option to use it with GPT-4 if you have the API.

Whether I'm writing my text in Pages, an email program, or on any website, I simply highlight my draft and directly insert the improved text into the corresponding text field using just a few keyboard commands through Writers brew AI. There's no need to open additional windows, and it doesn't require any additional mental effort. Furthermore, I have already automatically internalized the corresponding keyboard commands, so everything works effortlessly and like magic.

I want to emphasize once again that I hardly need direct access to GPT 4 or Chat-GPT for writing texts anymore, as everything can be done with Writers brew AI. Only for particularly difficult texts or when I want to delve into a topic brainstorm-style, do I still directly rely on GPT 4.

Edit:
"On July 6, 2023 , we gave all API users who have a history of successful payments access to the GPT-4 API (8k)"

OpenAI made the GPT-4 API available to all paying API customers. I am looking forward to being able to use Writer's Brew with GPT-4 now!

My Old Review from May:

Meanwhile, there have been some updates.

Now the application can be set so that the output language is identical to the input language. So, there are no more restrictions when using the application in German. Since the application can also be used with applications outside the web browser, I no longer need Google Chrome extensions and can directly and especially quickly access Writersbrew with keyboard commands.

This makes the application perfectly integrated into my workflow. For example, I wrote this text in German within Apple Pages. Before I post the text here, I can translate it to English with a mouse click without having to leave Apple Pages.
